<div id="review_1388437990" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1388437990" />
    <a title="Debojit Sengupta" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/38569584-debojit-sengupta"><img alt="Debojit Sengupta" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1614596521p2/38569584.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1388437990?book_show_action=true">Sep 10, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Debojit Sengupta" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Debojit Sengupta" href="/user/show/38569584-debojit-sengupta">Debojit Sengupta</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1388437990" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4489312988600762294">Read it if you want to get tortured. Some characters behave opposite to what the author describes them to be. Somewhere he says &quot;it was the perfect plan&quot; but I can clearly see its plain dumb. There is no buildup, things just randomly keep happening, almost all characters are unrealistic, most of the time you won&apos;t even understand their motivation. At places it seems as if the author forgot to introduce the character properly and would delve into his history at the wrong time and you would think </span>
  <span id="freeText4489312988600762294" style="display:none">Read it if you want to get tortured. Some characters behave opposite to what the author describes them to be. Somewhere he says "it was the perfect plan" but I can clearly see its plain dumb. There is no buildup, things just randomly keep happening, almost all characters are unrealistic, most of the time you won't even understand their motivation. At places it seems as if the author forgot to introduce the character properly and would delve into his history at the wrong time and you would think "why the hell am I being told this right now?". Women are scheming bitches and men are dogs. Offer them sex and they would suddenly forget caution,logic,reason and other stuff that keeps people alive. No more Sidney sheldon for me. Ever.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4489312988600762294" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


